I'm a health, philosophy and exercise enthusiast with love and passion for teaching. For the past five years, I've travelled extensively to many corners of the world to study the lifestyle, culture and knowledge each place has developed through thousands of years.

Living for extended periods of time in Thailand, India and China has primarily taught me the ways of life that I live by and speak on behalf of today. The act of getting to know oneself, finding out your passion and following your heart.

I'm a lifetime student of martial arts and devoted practitioner of yoga. The deep involvement of both these forms of exercise with philosophy and development of character has always inspired me to work just as hard on my inner self as my physical performance.

I teach physical exercise and wellbeing through my accumulated experience and studies, of which I call Body Alignment. It is my holistic approach to the natural movement of the human body where I draw upon gymnastics, calisthenics, Olympic lifting, martial arts and yoga combined to create a system to achieve full physical awareness and mobility.

I also have a blog (connectingdotstogether.com) where I write about my ideas of life through written text and poetry.
